User: An acute isosceles triangle, $ABC$, is inscribed in a circle.  Through $B$ and $C$, tangents to the circle are drawn, meeting at point $D$.  If $\angle ABC = \angle ACB = 2 \angle D$ and $\angle BAC = k \pi$ in radians, then find $k$.

[asy]
import graph;

unitsize(2 cm);

pair O, A, B, C, D;

O = (0,0);
A = dir(90);
B = dir(-30);
C = dir(210);
D = extension(B, B + rotate(90)*(B), C, C + rotate(90)*(C));

draw(Circle(O,1));
draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(B--D--C);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, SW);
label("$D$", D, S);
[/asy]
Assistant: <think>

